9FMjRr0gzjQk","label":"part of"},{"source":"recig8oK0LfpJJt76","target":"recgkzNX07a7kGFYL","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recig8oK0LfpJJt76","target":"reckKYeZ5P0KFuSkB","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recig8oK0LfpJJt76","target":"recMxoVUt13ExT48g","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recig8oK0LfpJJt76","target":"rec46MqJI7uxMvviP","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recig8oK0LfpJJt76","target":"recU1v1l7ZuJsuK0g","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recig8oK0LfpJJt76","target":"recSRPfTSaf7TsRiN","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recig8oK0LfpJJt76","target":"recgkFqZovgbr3pAi","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recig8oK0LfpJJt76","target":"recL1WV82pXaRBQ59","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recig8oK0LfpJJt76","target":"recKrSp5YmwkgRKv0","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recig8oK0LfpJJt76","target":"recjSyWPVWxolQ2r4","label":"event"},{"source":"recig8oK0LfpJJt76","target":"recZZnST3yj4b1akY","label":"event"},{"source":"recig8oK0LfpJJt76","target":"recltAvLmGRfERhYp","label":"event"}],"verses":[{"id":"recXUcJGSEGiAZn3U","ref":"Acts.25.1","text":"Now when Festus was come into the province, after three days he ascended from Caesarea to Jerusalem.","year":62},{"id":"rec2lluRmyFZfk6Ug","ref":"Acts.25.2","text":"Then the high priest and the chief of the Jews informed him against Paul, and besought him,","year":62},{"id":"rec5ZgjyUZWrSwIId","ref":"Acts.25.3","text":"And desired favour against him, that he would send for him to Jerusalem, laying wait in the way to kill him.","year":62},{"id":"recNUbRk0vwDzs5IS","ref":"Acts.25.4","text":"But Festus answered, that Paul should be kept at Caesarea, and that he himself would depart shortly thither.","year":62},{"id":"recvc0OSclcvOD9uv","ref":"Acts.25.5","text":"Let them therefore, said he, which among you are able, go down with me, and accuse this man, if there be any wickedness in him.","year":62},{"id":"recp5SpyrvwjmIuGd","ref":"Acts.25.6","text":"And when he had tarried among them more than ten days, he went down unto Caesarea; and the next day sitting on the judgment seat commanded Paul to be brought.","year":62},{"id":"recnl8vuWuD1WVgeY","ref":"Acts.25.7","text":"And when he was come, the Jews which came down from Jerusalem stood round about, and laid many and grievous complaints against Paul, which they could not prove.","year":62},{"id":"recyPoy2is6jUeA0I","ref":"Acts.25.8","text":"While he answered for himself, Neither against the law of the Jews, neither against the temple, nor yet against Caesar, have I offended any thing at all.","year":62}]}
